        {
            "review_id": "227317748",
            "steam_id": "76561198042408613",
            "playtime_minutes": 4584,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "I was a table top wargamer for a large part of my life painting up thousands of figurines. Today I can set up and play a battle using the WH series in a very small time frame. The resulting battles appear 'realistic' in terms of movement, battlefield control and tactics. The battlefields look realistic with the approach of enemy forces appearing in the distance spilling across the countryside. The campaign element is the strongest component of these games. The effect of terrain realistic and well imaged. The choice between symbolic and actual army movement very good, as are the many choices and outcomes in relation to towns and hamlets. The re-playability is sound, with lots of choice between different armies, regions and cultural strategies; and that is without the addition of a host of mods dowloadable from the steam workshop. Excellent games, hundreds of play hours ahead of me. If I live that long."
        },
